input_str: COMSTOCK PARK, MI - The West Michigan Whitecaps once again enjoyed fantastic pitching and broke open a close game with a pair of big innings and cruised to a 6-1 victory over the Great Lakes Loons on a brilliant Sunday afternoon in front of 6,702 at Fifth Third Ballpark. Whitecaps starter Alfred Gutierrez decided to record his first seven outs via the strikeout, and kept tallying more in seven innings of work. The 'Caps offense managed to squeeze a first inning run off Loons starter Riley Ottesen - who was making his Midwest League debut
